Grilled Cheese

Ingredients:
2 pieces of bread
1 piece of velveeta cheese
butter

1. Heat a 9' skillet on med high heat.

2. Butter 1 side of bread and put butter side down in skillet.

3. Place a piece of cheese on bread in skillet.

4. Butter other piece of bread and put butter side up on the cheese.

5. Cook until bread is getting golden brown and then turn to brown other side of bread.

6. Keep cooking until both sides of bread is golden brown and cheese is melted.

Enjoy!
